2. What is Blockchain?
Blockchain is a peer-to-peer, decentralized, and distributed system.
It is a cryptographically secure, append-only ledger that is immutable and updated through consensus among all participating nodes.
Key Characteristics:
‚Ä¢	Decentralized
‚Ä¢	Secure
‚Ä¢	Immutable
‚Ä¢	Transparent
‚Ä¢	Consensus-driven
________________________________________
3. Components of a Block
A block consists of two main parts:
3.1 Block Header
Contains:
‚Ä¢	Version of the block
‚Ä¢	Hash of the previous block
‚Ä¢	Merkle Root Hash
‚Ä¢	Timestamp of block creation
‚Ä¢	Nonce

3.2 Block Body
‚Ä¢	List of verified transactions
‚Ä¢	Nonce value added by the miner
Nonce:
A cryptographic value used to meet mining difficulty and add security.
________________________________________
4. Components of Blockchain
Block:
A container that stores:
‚Ä¢	Encrypted transaction data
‚Ä¢	Hash of the previous block
Chain:
‚Ä¢	Continuous list of blocks connected together
‚Ä¢	Each block stores the hash of the previous block
‚Ä¢	Ensures immutability and security
