10. Peer-to-Peer (P2P) Network
A network architecture where:
‚Ä¢	All nodes have equal responsibility
‚Ä¢	No central authority
‚Ä¢	Resources are shared directly
________________________________________
11. Centralized System
A system where one entity has full control over the network.
Examples:
‚Ä¢	Banking
‚Ä¢	Government Systems
‚Ä¢	Healthcare
‚Ä¢	Supply Chain
Drawbacks:
1.	Easily hacked
2.	Prone to fraud
3.	May cause financial crises
________________________________________
12. Distributed & Decentralized Systems
‚Ä¢	Resources and computation are shared
‚Ä¢	Decision-making is distributed
‚Ä¢	No single point of failure

Aspect	Centralized System	Distributed & Decentralized System
Definition	A system where data, control, and authority are managed by a single central entity.	A system where data, control, and decision-making are shared among multiple independent nodes.
Control	Single authority	Shared among participants
Architecture	Client‚ÄìServer	Peer-to-Peer (P2P)
Data Storage	Central database	Distributed across nodes
Transparency	Limited	High
Security Model	Authority-based	Cryptography + consensus
Immutability	Data can be altered	Data is append-only
Availability	Low during server failure	High availability
Scalability	Difficult	Easier
Trust Model	Trust in central authority	Trustless / distributed trust
Examples	Banking, Govt systems, Healthcare	Blockchain, P2P networks
