19. Three Pillars of Blockchain Technology
1.	Distributed Ledger
2.	Cryptography
3.	Consensus
________________________________________
1. Cryptography
Definition:
Cryptography is the science of securing information sent across two or more parties.
‚Ä¢	Algorithms are used to encrypt data
‚Ä¢	Secret keys are used for decryption
________________________________________
2. Consensus
Definition:
A method to ensure all nodes in a network verify transactions, agree on their order and existence, and prevent double spending.
________________________________________
3. Distributed Ledger
Definition:
A distributed ledger is a replicated, shared, synchronized digital database spread geographically across multiple sites and accessible by multiple participants.

 üîó Three Pillars of Blockchain Technology
Blockchain technology is built on three fundamental pillars that ensure trust, security, and decentralization without relying on a central authority.
Pillar	Definition	Key Features	Advantages	Examples	Real-World Use Case
