   ‚Üì
Verification by Other Miners
   ‚Üì
Block Added to Blockchain
________________________________________
Hashcash PoW System
‚Ä¢	Used by Bitcoin for mining
‚Ä¢	Hash problem includes:
o	Previous block hash
o	Set of transactions
o	Nonce
________________________________________27. Mining Pool
A mining pool is a group of miners who combine their computational power to increase the probability of successfully mining a block. The mining reward is shared among participants based on their contributed power.
________________________________________

1. Nonce
A nonce is a random number used in cryptographic hashing.
In blockchain, miners change the nonce repeatedly until the generated hash satisfies the network‚Äôs difficulty requirement.
________________________________________
2. Block
A block contains:
‚Ä¢	List of transactions
‚Ä¢	Hash of the previous block
‚Ä¢	Nonce
‚Ä¢	Timestamp
Blocks are linked together to form a secure and immutable blockchain.
________________________________________
